                <expan><abbr>Imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> Caesar Vespasianus <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>ustus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pontif</abbr><ex>ex</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>max</abbr><ex>imus</ex></expan> <lb n="2"/><expan><abbr>trib</abbr><ex>unicia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>pot</abbr><ex>estate</ex></expan> VII <expan><abbr>imp</abbr><ex>erator</ex></expan> XVII <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ater</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>atriae</ex></expan> co<expan><ex>n</ex><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ul</ex></expan> VII <expan><abbr>design</abbr><ex>atus</ex></expan> VIII <lb n="3"/>templum Matris Deum terrae motu conlapsum restituit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>(B): Horster 80: Z. 3: conlapsam.</p>
